 (float, int): &lt;function _operator.truediv(a, b, /)&gt;}</pre> <p>Multimethods introspect type annotations and use the name to find existing multimethods.</p> In [5]: Copied! <pre>import itertools
from collections.abc import Iterable, Sequence


@multimethod
def batched(values: Iterable, size):
    it = iter(values)
    return iter(lambda: list(itertools.islice(it, size)), [])


@multimethod
def batched(values: Sequence, size):
    for index in range(0, len(values), size):
        yield values[index : index + size]


